  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can you add money to a debit card from another card?",
  "response": "Adding money to a debit card from another card depends on the services and options provided by your bank or card issuer. Here are some common methods to do this:\n\n1. **Online Banking Transfer:**\n   - Log in to your online banking account or mobile app.\n   - Locate the option for transferring money or making payments.\n   - Select the account or card you want to transfer money from.\n   - Enter the details of the debit card or the account linked to it where you want to transfer the funds.\n   - Follow the instructions to complete the transfer.\n\n2. **ATM Transfer:**\n   - Visit an ATM that allows card-to-card transfers.\n   - Insert the card from which you want to transfer money and enter the PIN.\n   - Select the option for transferring funds.\n   - Enter the information for the debit card or account you want to transfer money to.\n   - Confirm the transaction.\n\n3. **Bank or Branch Visit:**\n   - Visit your bank branch in person.\n   - Provide the teller with both cards or the necessary details and request a transfer.\n   - The teller will guide you through the process and complete the transaction for you.\n\n4. **Payment Services:**\n   - Use a third-party payment service like PayPal, Venmo, or Cash App, if both cards are linked to accounts that support these services.\n   - Transfer the money to your account on the payment platform from one card and then transfer it to the account linked to the debit card.\n\n5. **Balance Transfer Services:**\n   - Some banks or financial institutions offer balance transfer services where you can transfer debt or funds from one card to another. Check if this service is available and applicable to your needs.\n\nAlways ensure that any transfers or transactions are conducted through secure and legitimate channels to protect your personal and financial information. If in doubt, consulting your bank or card issuer directly for guidance tailored to your specific situation is advisable.",
